<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3214] Strange Groovy bug for Maps in a Enums method</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3214</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This was originally reported on the Grails JIRA at&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GRAILS-3716&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GRAILS-3716&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Groovy version which has this bug is thus the one bundled with Grails-1.1-beta-1, not sure of the actual version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached app (Grails app) demonstrates the problem: call the something action on the main controller, and the assertion will fail. It is really strange, it seems the key of the Map is not &quot;taku&quot; but &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;taku&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux, Sun JDK 1.6.0.11</environment>
