                            <comment id="14466033" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2008 05:53:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I understand you right, then the relevant code should be &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;enum&lt;/span&gt; FontFamily
{
	ARIAL

	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void obtainMyMap()
	{
		Map map = [:]
		map[&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;taku&quot;&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;dio&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; map.taku == &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;dio&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
	}
}
FontFamily.obtainMyMap()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can reproduce the problem with that, the ARIAL element is not needed, the problem goes away if FonFamily is a normal class&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14465993" author="elvanor" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2008 05:59:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Exactly, you spotted the relevant code, and yes, the ARIAL element is not needed. And yes, this only happens with Enums, not classes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14465978" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2008 07:26:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
